  "body": "- [ yes] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nIf you use web3-provider-engine as your web3 provider, then try to do anything that fails at EVM level then the error message is always the same and is unrelated to the actual error\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. set up a `web3` using `web3-provider-engine` as the provider\r\n2. using an eth account with zero funds and `truffle-contract`, try to deploy a contract using `.new()`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nDeployment fails with good error message about insufficient funds\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nAn exception is throw with message `Web3ProviderEngine does not support synchronous requests.`\r\n\r\nThis appears to be due to this functions in reasons.js, which uses the synchronous `web3.currentProvider.send` function. I guess that can be updated to use an async call?\r\n\r\n```\r\n  /**\r\n   * Runs tx via `eth_call` and resolves a reason string if it exists on the response.\r\n   * @param  {Object} web3\r\n   * @return {String|Undefined}\r\n   */\r\n  get: function(params, web3){\r\n    const packet = {\r\n      jsonrpc: '2.0',\r\n      method: 'eth_call',\r\n      params: [params, 'latest'],\r\n      id: new Date().getTime(),\r\n    };\r\n\r\n    return new Promise(resolve => {\r\n      web3.currentProvider.send(packet, (err, response) => {\r\n        const reasonString = reason._extract(response, web3);\r\n        resolve(reasonString);\r\n      });\r\n    });\r\n  },\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System:  MacOS\r\n* Ethereum client: Infura\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): none (truffle-contract 4.0.25)\r\n* node version (`node --version`): 8.15.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): yarn version v1.16.0\r\n",
